===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κυβερνισμός]]''', '''[[κυβέρνησις]]''' (''kyvernismos'', ''kyvernesis'') "steering, pilotage, guiding", from '''[[κυβερνάω]]''' (''kyvernao'') "to steer, to drive, to guide, to act as a pilot".

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# the body with the power to make and/or enforce laws for a country, land area, people, or organization.
# the state and its administration viewed as the ruling political power.
# the management or control of a system.
# the tenure of a chief of state. 

